Reasoning: The paper deals with the optimization of wireless multi-user interfering systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-disciplines. The use of optimization algorithms and pricing mechanisms suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The focus on multi-agent systems and the use of convexification techniques suggests that the paper could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories. Finally, the mention of block-coordinate descent schemes suggests that the paper could belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) category.
